WEBVTT

00:09.211 --> 00:12.311
♪ (MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

00:16.812 --> 00:18.178
JOHN WILSON:
<i>Hey, New York.</i>

00:20.411 --> 00:21.611
<i>If you're like me,</i>

00:21.678 --> 00:25.078
<i>your pet slowly destroys</i>
<i>every single piece of furniture</i>

00:25.144 --> 00:27.111
<i>that you bring inside</i>
<i>of your apartment.</i>

00:28.144 --> 00:29.378
<i>This is Baby,</i>

00:29.445 --> 00:32.345
<i>and she is</i>
<i>a vicious little rascal</i>

00:32.411 --> 00:35.878
<i>that aggressively claws</i>
<i>and, um,</i>

00:35.945 --> 00:38.345
<i>vomits on everything I own.</i>

00:39.678 --> 00:42.311
<i>This makes it hard</i>
<i>to shop for anything nice.</i>

00:42.378 --> 00:45.511
<i>Because it's guaranteed</i>
<i>that I won't be able</i>

00:45.578 --> 00:47.211
<i>to preserve my furniture</i>

00:47.278 --> 00:50.411
<i>for longer</i>
<i>than a couple of months.</i>

00:50.478 --> 00:53.011
<i>There's a bunch of things</i>
<i>you could do to deter your cat</i>

00:53.078 --> 00:54.511
<i>from defiling your stuff,</i>

00:54.578 --> 00:57.678
<i>but a lot of them</i>
<i>have mixed results.</i>

00:57.745 --> 01:00.578
<i>You could try to coat</i>
<i>your furniture in citrus,</i>

01:00.645 --> 01:03.845
<i>which cats, uh, supposedly hate.</i>

01:03.912 --> 01:06.945
<i>But if you also hate</i>
<i>the smell of lemon, uh,</i>

01:07.011 --> 01:10.378
<i>this can be a cruel punishment</i>
<i>for the both of you.</i>

01:10.445 --> 01:13.712
<i>You can try putting tape</i>
<i>over their favorite areas.</i>

01:13.778 --> 01:16.445
<i>But this may end up causing</i>
<i>the animal to relocate</i>

01:16.511 --> 01:18.578
<i>to new areas on your furniture</i>

01:18.645 --> 01:21.044
<i>that, uh,</i>
<i>aren't covered in tape.</i>

01:22.745 --> 01:25.411
<i>You can try getting</i>
<i>a scratching pole, uh,</i>

01:25.478 --> 01:28.578
<i>but they might not end up</i>
<i>using it at all.</i>

01:28.645 --> 01:30.812
<i>But that's okay,</i>
<i>because you can always turn it</i>

01:30.878 --> 01:32.511
<i>into a hat rack...</i>

01:32.578 --> 01:34.178
(TRUMPET BLARING)

01:34.244 --> 01:35.878
JOHN: <i>A hat rack.</i>

01:35.945 --> 01:38.078
<i>So, if none</i>
<i>of these options work,</i>

01:38.144 --> 01:41.178
<i>and you find yourself</i>
<i>just counting down the days</i>

01:41.244 --> 01:43.678
<i>until one of you passes away,</i>

01:43.745 --> 01:47.244
<i>furniture covers</i>
<i>might be your best bet.</i>

01:47.311 --> 01:49.144
<i>So buckle up, buster,</i>

01:49.211 --> 01:52.545
<i>because things are about to get</i>
<i>pretty wet, pretty wild.</i>

01:55.712 --> 01:57.778
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:58.645 --> 02:00.044
JOHN:
<i>Now, a lot of people think</i>

02:00.111 --> 02:02.745
<i>that plastic furniture covers</i>
<i>are unsightly</i>

02:02.812 --> 02:04.945
<i>and will judge you</i>
<i>for your choice.</i>

02:05.011 --> 02:07.611
<i>So, before you do anything</i>
<i>you might regret,</i>

02:07.678 --> 02:09.511
<i>uh, first you're gonna need</i>
<i>to be confident</i>

02:09.578 --> 02:11.611
<i>in your sense of taste.</i>

02:11.678 --> 02:13.445
♪ (QUIET MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:13.511 --> 02:16.011
<i>Everyone likes to think</i>
<i>that they have good taste,</i>

02:16.078 --> 02:18.211
<i>but this is impossible,</i>

02:18.278 --> 02:21.178
<i>because you can't have</i>
<i>good taste without bad taste.</i>

02:22.244 --> 02:23.845
<i>What is beautiful to you</i>

02:23.912 --> 02:27.078
<i>might be revolting</i>
<i>to someone else.</i>

02:27.144 --> 02:29.845
<i>And it's almost impossible</i>
<i>for good and bad taste</i>

02:29.912 --> 02:32.011
<i>to peacefully coexist.</i>

02:33.111 --> 02:35.812
<i>This is what makes people</i>
<i>who use plastic covers,</i>

02:35.878 --> 02:37.378
<i>uh, such a rare breed.</i>

02:38.278 --> 02:40.144
<i>They buy</i>
<i>very dignified furniture,</i>

02:40.211 --> 02:42.945
<i>worthy of a showroom</i>
<i>or a museum,</i>

02:43.011 --> 02:46.211
<i>but in order to extend its life,</i>
<i>have decided to cover it</i>

02:46.278 --> 02:48.678
<i>with one of</i>
<i>the most inelegant materials</i>

02:48.745 --> 02:51.812
<i>known to man-- humankind.</i>

02:51.878 --> 02:55.111
<i>But at the same time,</i>
<i>any lifestyle depraved enough</i>

02:55.178 --> 02:58.311
<i>to require a permanent shield</i>
<i>against liquids</i>

02:58.378 --> 03:00.678
<i>is, uh, worthy of respect.</i>

03:00.745 --> 03:01.912
